{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0a9caa5f-04ba-48b5-b6fc-290127c254d7","content":"In your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created   += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Activated += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped   += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Resumed   += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Destroying += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n\n    // Size/position changes\n    window.SizeChanged += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine($\"SizeChanged: {window.Width}x{window.Height}\");\n\n    // Background/foreground (available on mobile)\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Typical lifecycle order:**\n\n| Platform | Sequence |\n|---|---|\n| **Launch** | `Created → Activated` |\n| **Backgrounded** | `Deactivated → Stopped` |\n| **Restored** | `Resumed → Activated` |\n| **Closed** | `Deactivated → Stopped → Destroying` |\n\n> **Tip:** `Backgrounding` fires only on iOS/Android. Use `Stopped` for cross-platform background detection.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4c289944-0ca3-45b3-a07c-2d2be62b6980","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI Window lifecycle events and how to subscribe to them for logging/debugging. This is a general knowledge question — I can answer directly without needing to explore any codebase.","outputTokens":453},"id":"4d78e7f2-8ad5-43f4-9797-8bec1567af0b","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:45:39.954Z","parentId":"853bd05a-4a38-4b42-809f-db35d053fd29"}
